{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1772071105,"nonce":"0/SSgTlFnxdij31g2jxMMF3hTwg=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOQ241x87t_V9Y","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/263","origin":"github"},"title":"Simplify scripts and Makefile interface","message":"## Problem\n\nThe workspace has 42 scripts in \\`.agent/scripts/\\` and a Makefile with 19 targets. Most Makefile targets are thin wrappers around shell scripts, creating two-layer indirection (Makefile → script → colcon) without providing Make's core value proposition (dependency-based incremental builds).\n\nUsers and agents face cognitive overhead figuring out which entry point to use for a given task.\n\n## Prior work\n\n- [Issue #252](https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/252) / [PR #254](https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/pull/254): Script and Makefile intent recovery — documented the purpose and design intent of all existing scripts and targets at \\`.agent/work-artifacts/issue-252-script-intents.md\\`\n- [Issue #249 research](https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/249), §1–2: Evaluated \\`just\\`, \\`task\\`, and \\`mise\\` as Makefile alternatives; analyzed self-documenting Makefile patterns\n- [Issue #249 research](https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/249), §4: Script consolidation patterns — categorization framework, subcommand pattern analysis\n\n## Scope\n\n1. **Audit scripts** — categorize as user-facing, internal, or dead code using the intent recovery document as input\n2. **Decide: improve Makefile or migrate to \\`just\\`** — the research evaluated both options; either is viable\n3. **Reduce entry points** — consolidate related scripts, expand the \\`agent\\` subcommand pattern, remove dead code\n4. **Ensure \\`make help\\` or \\`just --list\\` is self-documenting** — the interface should explain itself\n\n## Constraints\n\n- Guided by [Principle #5: Radical simplicity](https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/blob/feature/issue-249/docs/PRINCIPLES.md) — don't add complexity to reduce complexity\n- Guided by [Principle #7: Improve incrementally](https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/blob/feature/issue-249/docs/PRINCIPLES.md) — can be done in stages\n\n---\n**Authored-By**: \\`Claude Code Agent\\`\n**Model**: \\`Claude Opus 4.6\\`","files":null}]}